	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Dueling:<BR>
<BR>
Try some freaking sense. Casters have low HP, why waste time rooting. If you are a high level wizard, you do not use your huge nuke on a caster. That is suicide. Try using your Level 12 Lightning Shock spell for ONE type of attack. It is quick and disrupts casters and does not have the same resist rates as Tishans Clash does. Do NOT use Tishan Clash in a duel. The time casting that spell can be used more effecitively casting a DD spell because it is almost always resisted in a duel ...same with root at higher levels. If the pet is really annoying you than Shadow Step and wait for the pet to come to you. The necro will have to follow his pet ...it is faster. While the pet is running to you, blast it ...root it and blast, you decide.<BR>
<BR>
When fighting a necro, cast two or three short lasting dummy spells on yourself and then buff yourself. The necros DOTs will fill in the top spots which Cancel/Nullify Magic attempts to cancel first. So reserve a memorized spell slot for Cancel/Nullify Magic. If the pet won't let you get off Cancel/Nullify Magic, Shadow Step/Yonder. We used to have a spell that would face you in the direction of all summoned creatures including PC pets, which ruled for duels. I have been away from the game for a long time and I think the pets no longer come in as a viable target.<BR>
<BR>
You really only need to nuke the hell out of a necro w/ short casting spells.<BR>
<BR>
Other Pointers for Dueling:<BR>
- Build up your Magic Save - not just for dueling<BR>
- Keep Shadow Step and Cancel/Nullify Magic mem'd<BR>
- Keep 1 Cold, 1 Hot, and 1 Magic spell mem'd<BR>
- Keep Skin line mem'd<BR>
- Keep Root/Snare mem'd<BR>
- Keep Harvest mem'd if you have it<BR>
- Skin line does NOT protect you from interupts in spell casting<BR>
- Keep your cool<BR>
<BR>
Enchanters are the tuffest to duel, but if your Magic Sv is high than you shouldn't have too much problem. After level 35, each time you cast a spell you roll for the lowest resist possible. Sometimes you roll in the middle and sometimes you get the worst resist, but it is an advantage we have that the others do not.<BR>
<BR>
Just remember ...wizards do damage quickly and since casters have the lowest amount of HP they are actually the easiest, save the Enchanter.<BR>
<BR>
There, now that I provided some info to back my claim up I will say this again...<BR>
<BR>
If you can't beat a necro, you suck.<BR>
<BR>
Even though I no longer play the game I think I will keep my favorite tricks to myself rather than giving the necros reading this board the chance to think of a defense to them. Just remember what we do best and that some of your least used spells can actually be your best in a PvP fight.<BR>
<BR>
And for you necros, have fun being a mere mana battery as the older you get. he he heh!<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Shadowfax
				</font>
